<subSubSection id="C322B4E76662FFD2FF0B067169639A69" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6662FFD2FF0B06716CF199D5" blockId="4.[151,1436,353,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6662FFD2FF0B0671696F996D" bold="true" box="[151,305,353,380]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is relatively common throughout the northern GOM. Commonly reported as a coastal species inhabiting shallow waters from the shore out to approximately 
<quantity id="4CC04A896662FFD2FC5D06966BA399B1" box="[961,1021,390,416]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
, although individuals of this species have been documented during NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys out to approximately 
<quantity id="4CC04A896662FFD2FBB506BA6C3C99D5" box="[1065,1122,426,452]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" unit="m" value="90.0">90 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6662FFD2FF5B06DD69639A69" blockId="4.[151,1436,353,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6662FFD2FF5B06DD69DB99F9" bold="true" box="[199,389,461,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">First Record in</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B50ED316662FFD2FE0C06DD6A149A21" collectionCode="GOM, MCZ" location="However" municipality="Louis Agassiz" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Florida">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6662FFD2FE0C06DD698399F9" bold="true" box="[400,477,461,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<collectionCode id="ED297FA96662FFD2FE0C06DD698699F9" box="[400,472,461,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">GOM</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="548359CE6662FFD2FD8206DE6A1099F9" box="[542,590,462,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">type</typeStatus>
specimen (
<collectionCode id="ED297FA96662FFD2FD4906DE6B4A99F9" box="[725,788,462,488]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="Museum">MCZ</collectionCode>
S-97) described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6662FFD2FB9906DE6CEA99F9" author="Garman, S." box="[1029,1204,462,488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" pagination="167 - 172" refId="ref17218" refString="Garman, S. (1880) New species of selachians in the museum collection. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 6 (11), 167 - 172." type="journal article" year="1880">Garman (1880)</bibRefCitation>
was collected from 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6662FFD2FF0B06E268B69A1D" box="[151,232,498,524]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Florida</collectingRegion>
by 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BE37D166662FFD2FE8806E269EA9A1D" box="[276,436,498,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Louis Agassiz</collectingMunicipality>
in 1853. 
<location id="8EE7B1B76662FFD2FDBD06E26AD79A1D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0391567A6662FFD2FF0B078A6ADC9AF5:8EE7B1B76662FFD2FDBD06E26AD79A1D" box="[545,649,498,524]" municipality="Louis Agassiz" name="However" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" stateProvince="Florida">However</location>
, it is not stated from where in 
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6662FFD2FC7A06E26C699A1D" box="[998,1079,498,524]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Florida</collectingRegion>
the specimen was collected, so it may or may not have come from the
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B50ED316662FFD2FDCE05066DC29A21" box="[594,1436,534,560]" collectionCode="GOM" location="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Florida">
<collectionCode id="ED297FA96662FFD2FDCE05066AC99A21" box="[594,663,534,560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">GOM</collectionCode>
. 
<location id="8EE7B1B76662FFD2FD3D05066A939A21" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0391567A6662FFD2FF0B078A6ADC9AF5:8EE7B1B76662FFD2FD3D05066A939A21" box="[673,717,534,560]" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" stateProvince="Florida">The</location>
first definitive account of this species occurring in the northern
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B50ED316662FFD2FF0B052A69669A69" collectionCode="GOM" location="West" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" specimenCode="USNM 5158" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Florida">
<collectionCode id="ED297FA96662FFD2FF0B052A68869A45" box="[151,216,570,596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">GOM</collectionCode>
is from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6662FFD2FEA2052A6A0F9A45" author="Goode, G. B. &amp; Bean, T. H." box="[318,593,570,596]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" pagination="183 - 226" refId="ref17612" refString="Goode, G. B. &amp; Bean, T. H. (1883) Reports on the results of dredging under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, on the east coast of the United States, during the summer of 1880, by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer Blake, Commander J. R. Bartlett, U. S. N., commanding. Report on the fishes. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 10, 183 - 226." type="journal article" year="1883">Goode and Bean (1883)</bibRefCitation>
referencing a specimen collected from 
<location id="8EE7B1B76662FFD2FB87052A6C0C9A45" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0391567A6662FFD2FF0B078A6ADC9AF5:8EE7B1B76662FFD2FB87052A6C0C9A45" box="[1051,1106,570,596]" name="West" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" stateProvince="Florida">West</location>
<collectingRegion id="49FC298E6662FFD2FBC7052A6CF29A45" box="[1115,1196,570,596]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Florida</collectingRegion>
(
<specimenCode id="DB9E4F176662FFD2FB21052A6D0D9A45" box="[1213,1363,569,596]" collectionCode="USNM" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="Museum">USNM 5158</specimenCode>
) at an unknown date
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B4E76662FFD2FF5B05926ADC9AF5" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6662FFD2FF5B059268A29AD1" blockId="4.[151,1436,353,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6662FFD2FF5B059269659A8D" bold="true" box="[199,315,642,668]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Remarks.</emphasis>
Despite being relatively common in shallow waters, this species is little studied and requires focused research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6662FFD2FF5B05D96ADC9AF5" blockId="4.[151,1436,353,740]" box="[199,642,713,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6662FFD2FF5B05D9699E9AF5" bold="true" box="[199,448,713,740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Near Threatened
</paragraph>
